&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Savoy Life is a technology-enabled healthcare services startup focused on making healthcare work for seniors and their caregivers. We exist because the senior population is exploding, medical spend is already out of control, and poorly coordinated care is wasting tens of billions of dollars every year. At the same time, the two resources we need most to address this problem - caregivers and primary care providers - are stretched thinner than ever.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Savoy aims to make aging better by restoring agency to seniors and integrating caregiving into the heart of healthcare to allow seniors to spend more quality days at home - and fewer days in the hospital. Today, this includes going into individual homes as well as partnering with senior living communities to coordinate and manage clinical gaps for these seniors, their caregivers, and the care ecosystem. Savoy deploys a team of clinical experts both in-person and virtually paired with proprietary technology to drive clinical outcomes – without disrupting the current care.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Savoy Life:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Savoy Life is a healthcare startup focused on improving senior living. Savoy Life’s model of care aims to support&amp;nbsp;senior living communities and help tie residents, their caregivers, and the providers within the community together. This is done by partnering with senior living communities to coordinate and manage clinical gaps for residents to improve these community’s core business drivers. We deploy our own team of​ clinical experts both in-person and virtually paired with technology to provide instant leverage and relief for the community’s staff and fill gaps in care not always met by existing providers in the community. We honor residents’ existing care team including primary care via wraparound services to​ give residents the high-quality care and support they deserve, on​ their terms.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Savoy Life General Application:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Don&#39;t see the right role, however believe in our mission, and feel you could contribute to our team? Submit an application to our General Application.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be sure to include contact information, resume, and/or cover letter to tell us about your job interest and experience and to be considered for a future openings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;Mission&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;We make healthcare&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;work&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;for seniors and their caregivers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vision&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;To make aging better for everyone by restoring agency to seniors and integrating caregiving into the heart of healthcare—so that every moment leads to smarter decisions, greater dignity, and better outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;x_MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Values&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Engage&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;We foster genuine human connections by listening deeply, building trust, and approaching every interaction with empathy and respect—always assuming positive intent.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Empower&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;We lift seniors, caregivers, and our team by embracing change, encouraging autonomy, and going above and beyond to support meaningful choice and confidence.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Simplify&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;We cut through complexity to create clear, accessible, and compassionate care—imagining new ways to make healthcare work better for everyone.&lt;/p&gt;
