&lt;p&gt;Savoy Life is seeking a healthcare relationship and growth-focused Partner Success &amp;amp; Market Development Manager to drive senior engagement, provide customer success support with existing customers, build a care network, and drive growth with new customers. This is a hybrid role including field work to directly engage the staff and seniors inside senior living communities as well as through other referral sources such as home health, hospice, hospitals, and beyond. Additionally, this role includes building and engaging with other community partners (such as primary care provider groups and healthcare brokers) bridging this gap with these resources and the local Savoy clinical team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Market Development&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meet and exceed set business development targets with senior living communities as well as developing a referral network to drive senior engagement via other settings (such as individual homes, adult family homes, etc.) in your region&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize cold calling, in-person drop-ins, and other prospecting techniques to identify and obtain new customers and referrals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and sustain a strong brand for Savoy Life in the market through attending, hosting, presenting at local events and more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For senior living community customers, support a smooth transition from contracting through launch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain documentation hygiene by activities and contacts in Savoy’s CRM platform and other technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Patient Engagement&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive patient engagement with seniors by deploying an array of strategies to obtain consents from seniors and Power of Attorney&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner Success / Account Management&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a trusted relationship with customers to support their current and anticipated needs including the Executive Director, Marketing/Sales Director and Health &amp;amp; Wellness Director&lt;/li&gt;
