&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct assessments, ongoing check-ins, and other in-person care for residents within senior living communities and other senior setting to identify and support care needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist Savoy’s Advanced Practice Providers in developing and implementing chronic condition care plans in collaboration with the clinical team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate care for residents through collaboration with rimary care providers, specialists, POAs/families, and other care services to ensure seamless patient care delivery. Note for senior living communities, this include community Health and Wellness Directors and other community staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with an internal team including a local Resident Care Coordinator, Partner Success leader, and virtual Advanced Practice Provider.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate and detailed documentation in Savoy Life&#39;s Electronic Medical Record (EMR) and other technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Triage after hours patient inbound phone calls to further support care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide clinical expertise and act as a resource for on-site staff to support high-quality resident care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate with flexibility and adaptability in a new and evolving role within a growing startup organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active Registered Nurse (RN) license in Washington.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must possess a valid and current driver&#39;s license.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong background in geriatric/senior care, with a focus on care assessments and care coordination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in care planning for chronic conditions, including collaboration with interdisciplinary teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent documentation and electronic medical record-keeping skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work autonomously, manage ambiguity, solve problems, and adapt to new processes as the role and organization evolve.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in working in senior living facilities is highly desirable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
